  "datePublished": "2026-03-03",
  "description": "Federation is the horizontal coordination of autonomous groups through delegates who carry revocable mandates, not permanent representatives who accumulate decision-making power. Each participating group retains its autonomy; the federation coordinates action across groups without subordinating any to a central authority.",
